Class STAFHelperCompatible3

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    STAFHelperCompatibleInterface

    public class STAFHelperCompatible3
extends AbstractSTAFHelperCompatible
     Contains the specific implementation related to STAF3.
 Be careful to import this class into other class or use the static methods 
 of this class in other class, which will cause the backward compatibility problem.
 
 To get an instance of this class, use AbstractSTAFHelperCompatible.getCompatibleSTAF(int).

      • getUnMarshallResult

        public static com.ibm.staf.STAFMarshallingContext getUnMarshallResult(java.lang.String result)
        From STAF3.3, the result returned from submit will be marshaled String.
        We need to un-marshal it to get the structure for human to understand.
        The returned structure STAFMarshallingContext need to be parsed. Click the link to see how to parse it.
        Parameters:
        result -
        Returns:
        STAFMarshallingContext, if result can't be un-marshaled, null is returned.
        See Also:
        #submit(String, String, String)

      • getServiceEvents

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getServiceEvents(java.lang.String machine,
                                                java.lang.String servicename)
                                                  throws SAFSException
        Description copied from interface: STAFHelperCompatibleInterface
        According to the service name, we try to get all events related to it.
        servicename - String, the service we want to get events for
        Returns:
        List of events related to the service, each list-item contains the event's name, state, number of waiters. The format is not the same for STAF2 and STAF3
        Throws:
        SAFSException

      • getRunningEngineNames

        public java.util.Collection getRunningEngineNames(java.lang.String machine)
                                           throws SAFSException
        Get collection of running Engine names. We parse the STAF command: staf local SEM list EVENT
        We deduce the number of unique <engine>Ready or <engine>Running events. We return the collection of unique engine names.
        Returns:
        Collection (Vector) of String engine names( ex: SAFS/RobotJ, SAFS/SELENIUM, etc..)
        Throws:
        SAFSException
